UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199684900084
AB  - This paper explores an equilibrium imperfect information model of the business cycle under floating exchange rates with perfect international capital mobility. While international trade in goods takes place in decentralized markets, foreign exchange and international debt are traded in centralized markets. The paper investigates the degree of international business cycle synchronization, the covariation between the exchange rate and the terms of trade and the degree of insulation provided by floating exchange rates. In sharp contrast to sticky price Keynesian type models, unanticipated monetary shocks will induce synchronized cycles, given sufficient elasticity conditions. The amplitude of the business cycle will depend upon the covariance matrix of stochastic schocks.
