AB  - We construct a pair of linear examples to study the collapse time of a fixed exchange-rate regime. The first example is a perfect-foresight, continuous-time model which allows calculation of the exact collapse time and the tracking of reserves. The second example is a discrete time, stochastic model which yields an endogenous probability distribution over the collapse time and produces a forward discount of the exchange rate.
